The Czech energy regulator opposes
a plan to set a guaranteed price for electricity generated by
new reactors at the Temelin nuclear power plant,  Hospodarske
Noviny  reported, citing Alena Vitaskova, who heads the watchdog.  Industry and Trade Minister Martin Kuba supports a
guaranteed purchase price as  CEZ AS (CEZ) , the countryâ€™s biggest
electricity generator, looks at ways to finance construction of
two new reactors at Temelin, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
